---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="About - Map the Wild">
  <main class="relative z-10 max-w-2xl mx-auto px-6 py-16 md:py-24">
    <h1 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-display text-ink mb-12">
      About
    </h1>

    <article class="about-prose">
      <p>
        I used to think you figured things out, then built them. Like a slab of marble. Pretty backwards, and probably says a lot about who I was.
      </p>

      <p>
        I put this together to connect the things that hover at the edges of my curiosity. <em>inter-legere</em>.
      </p>

      <p>
        Let's see what we can gather, for this pyre of the mind.
      </p>

      <p style="padding-top: var(--space-xl);">
        <a href="/mapthewild/islands">
          Explore the territories &rarr;
        </a>
      </p>
    </article>
  </main>
</Layout>

<style>
  .about-prose {
    font-size: 16px;
    line-height: 1.8;
    color: var(--color-ink-light);
  }

  .about-prose p {
    margin-bottom: var(--space-lg);
  }

  .about-prose code {
    color: var(--color-ochre);
    background: var(--color-parchment-dark);
    padding: 2px 6px;
    border-radius: 3px;
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 14px;
  }

  .about-prose a {
    color: var(--color-ochre);
    text-decoration: none;
    transition: color 0.2s;
  }

  .about-prose a:hover {
    text-decoration: underline;
  }
</style>
